Patch summary:
Set release aconfig defaults needed by the desktop build. Quick Settings stays
on the known-good non-Compose path because the desktop QS customizations target
the classic implementation, including the tile removals and panel interaction
behavior used by this VM.

This also enables Launcher3 desktop visual-effect flags in the generated
release flag sets. Keeping those values here makes the behavior reproducible
across both trunk staging and BP4A-style builds instead of depending on runtime
flag edits after first boot.

LineageOS 23.2 selects the stable BP4A target. Carry the remaining desktop
windowing values into that release config as read-only values so stable Android
16 builds keep the same desktop behavior without masquerading as a
trunk-staging preview build.

diff --git a/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/enable_large_desktop_windowing_tile_flag_values.textproto b/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/enable_large_desktop_windowing_tile_flag_values.textproto
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/aconfig/bp4a/com.android.launcher3/enable_large_desktop_windowing_tile_flag_values.textproto
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+flag_value {
+  package: "com.android.launcher3"
+  name: "enable_large_desktop_windowing_tile"
+  state: ENABLED
+  permission: READ_ONLY
+}
